People ask me all the time how I Find my Balance as a Married Father of Three that manages multiple Businesses 😩

First off, Mahalo for a great time Hawaii 🙏🏾💯! I was on a much needed vacation, but y’all already know my mind was on business, especially franchising. I noticed these three franchise concepts found the right opportunity in Hawaii of all places, and here’s why. 

1) McDonald’s: they went in and saturated the market from a American fast food perspective early and has held a market share. There is no other global fast food chain with nearly the amount of units in Hawaii as McDonald’s. They serve a specific demographic that enjoys eating American food and don’t have other great options so all the money comes to them!

2. The UPS Store: Logistics, and transportation aren’t the best and cheapest on an island. The UPS store is one of the only solid options that offers shipping to that mainland and across the world. Ground transportation obviously does not exist. So the customer has to come and utilize the services of this great franchise concept.

3: Primerica Financial Services: a life insurance franchise is more sexy than you think! Notice the numbers I put up about how many locations serve the general population there. There are only three locations per 100,000 people! That means that you have a plethora of people that need life insurance and you would be one of the only ones offering that within their region. Less competition = more food for you to eat.

They say 96% of all entrepreneurs don’t put their children to work 🤯!!

I’m out in the field a lot and the guilt trip of not being around on some days unbearable. In all actuality, putting them to work in OUR business provides even more quality time spent and the first-hand knowledge they get to gain about operating the actual business 💯. 

For example, with our @turo business, they need to understand the route of acquiring each car under the family business, the process of preparation to be listed online, the detail taken into providing great service, time management, scheduling whilst multi-tasking, etc. 

They can only learn this by doing! They can delegate the tasks once they have stabilized the operation. 

I have always had my sons alongside me in all of my ventures. My oldest son Kingston has been in investment group meetings as young as two months old! 

To be honest, I really had no choice but to take him to these meetings, but it was well worth it as I look back in it now. The goal is to have them work in the business, fall in love with the business, make entrepreneurship a passion, and take over/operate the business on behalf of the family.

Again, here’s to consistency, and not perfection!
